AN ACT relating to education; revising provisions relating to the State Seal of
Civics Program; creating the Advisory Council on Civics Education;
establishing the membership and duties of the Council; making an
appropriation to the Nevada Center for Civic Engagement to raise
awareness of and create awards for civics education; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, the Superintendent of Public Instruction is required to: (1) establish a
2 State Seal of Civics Program to recognize pupils who graduate high school with a high level
3 of proficiency in civics; (2) create a State Seal of Civics to affix to the diploma of such pupils;
4 (3) establish the criteria for the Program; and (4) adopt regulations that set forth the criteria to
5 designate a school, pupil or teacher or other school employee as a Nevada School of Civic
6 Excellence, Student Civic Leader or Educator Civic Leader, respectively. (NRS 388.5933,
7 388.5935, 388.5937) Section 2 of this bill creates the Advisory Council on Civics Education
8 within the Department of Education and sets forth the provisions for [appointment to]
9 membership and service on the Council. Section 3 of this bill requires the Council to: (1)
10 assist the Superintendent with the development and implementation of the State Seal of Civics
11 Program; and (2) develop and set forth certain criteria for the Program. Section 4 of this bill:
12 (1) requires the Superintendent to develop the Program in cooperation with the Council; (2)
13 authorizes the Superintendent, in consultation with the Council, to adopt any regulations
14 necessary to carry out the provisions of the Program; and (3) authorizes the Superintendent to
15 apply for any available grants and accept any donations or gifts for the support of the
16 Program. Section 5 of this bill revises the grade point average and examination requirements
17 for a pupil to receive the State Seal of Civics. Sections 5 and 6 of this bill revise provisions of
18 the Program to account for the duties of the Council.
19 Section 7 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Nevada Center for Civic Engagement
20 to raise awareness of civics education programs and create awards in areas of civics
21 education.

