1 Section 1. Chapter 388 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. The Advisory Council on Civics Education is hereby created
4 within the Department of Education. The Council consists of:
5 (a) The Secretary of State or his or her designee;
6 (b) Two members who are appointed by the Governor, one of whom is a
7 representative of a business in this State and one of whom is a representative of
8 an industry in this State;
9 (c) Two members who are appointed by the Superintendent of Public
10 Instruction and who are employees of the Department;
11 [(b)] (d) Two members who are appointed by the Executive Director of the
12 Nevada Center for Civic Engagement and who are staff members of the Nevada
13 Center for Civic Engagement or its successor organization;
14 [(c)] (e) One member who is appointed by the Chancellor of the Nevada
15 System of Higher Education;
16 (f) One member who is appointed by the Nevada Association of School
17 Administrators who is a principal of a public high school;
18 [(d)] (g) One member who is appointed by the Clark County Education
19 Association and who is a teacher in a public high school in an urban setting in
20 southern Nevada; and
21 [(e)] (h) One member who is appointed by the Nevada State Education
22 Association and who is a teacher in a public high school in a rural setting or in
23 northern Nevada.
24 2. After the initial terms, the term of each member of the Council appointed
25 pursuant to paragraphs (b) to (h), inclusive, of subsection 1 is 2 years, and
26 members shall serve at the pleasure of their appointing authority.
27 3. Any vacancy occurring in the membership of the Council must be filled
28 in the same manner as the original appointment not later than 30 days after the
29 vacancy occurs.
30 4. The Council shall select from its members a Chair and a Vice Chair who
31 shall hold office for 1 year and who may be reselected.
32 5. The Council shall meet at the call of the Chair as often as necessary to
33 perform its duties pursuant to section 3 of this act.
34 6. A majority of the members of the Council constitutes a quorum for the
35 transaction of business, and a majority of those members present at any meeting
36 is sufficient for any official action taken by the Council.
37 7. The members of the Council serve without compensation, except that
38 each member is entitled to receive the per diem allowance and travel expenses
39 provided for state officers and employees generally while engaged in the official
40 business of the Council.
41 8. A member of the Council who is an officer or employee of this State or a
42 political subdivision of this State must be relieved from his or her duties without
43 loss of regular compensation to prepare for and attend meetings of the Council
44 and perform any work necessary to carry out the duties of the Council in the most

